## Phase 5: Update PR Description with Test Report

Once all tests pass, update the PR description (using `update_pull_request`) by appending the following sections to the existing auto-generated body:

### 5.1 Test Execution Report Table
```markdown
### 🧪 Test Execution Report

| Step | Interaction | Result | Duration |
|------|------------|--------|----------|
| 1 | <TEST_ID>OrderImport | ✅ PASSED | Xs |
| 2 | <TEST_ID>CashSaleImport | ✅ PASSED | Xs |
| 3 | <TEST_ID>RefundImport | ✅ PASSED | Xs |

**Test Suites:** 1 passed, 1 total
**Tests:** N passed, N total
**Total Time:** Xs

**Report:** [Reporting Portal](<URL from test output>)
```

### 5.2 Fixes Summary Table
List all issues found and fixed during review:
```markdown
### 🔧 Fixes Applied During Review

| # | Category | Issue | Fix |
|---|----------|-------|-----|
| 1 | Naming | <description> | <fix applied> |
| 2 | Expected Values | <description> | <fix applied> |
```

### 5.3 File Structure Update
Update the `📂 File Structure` section if files were renamed or the suite directory changed.

